In this article, it is stated that the President of the United States held a meeting with his international health and national security teams to discuss the ongoing Ebola crisis in West Africa. The President was briefed on the current situation in the region and the measures being taken to end the epidemic in Sierra Leone and Guinea. He emphasized the importance of reaching zero Ebola cases and instructed his team to remain involved in order to prevent future outbreaks from becoming epidemics. The article also mentions that the U.S. Government will continue its efforts to fight against Ebola until all cases in the affected countries are contained.